For KTDA Stakeholders

ChaiMetrics is designed to support factory managers, extension officers, and KTDA programme teams with data-driven tools for farm performance monitoring. The platform does not replace field knowledge — it augments it by surfacing patterns across large numbers of farms that would be difficult to track manually.

Insights are generated in plain language and are intended to be interpretable without a technical background. If you are a KTDA stakeholder interested in a demonstration or data partnership, please reach out via the contact details below.
Email - mogakanewton0@gmail.com

Contributing

This project is in active development. If you are a developer interested in contributing — particularly in areas of ML model improvement, frontend UX, or KTDA data integration — feel free to open an issue or submit a pull request.

